For this question, you will write a program that assemble a valid
SMTP message.  Your program should be named smtp, and may be a
script or a compiled program.

We will invoke your program as

    ./smtp -m <from addr> -t <to addr> -s <subject> -f <message file> [<attachment>...]

The SMTP message should then be written to STDOUT, including all
necessary headers and properly formatted.

For example, we might call your program with a simple message body
as

    ./smtp -m tservo@gizmonic.cs.umd.edu -t ctrobot@gizmonic.cs.umd.edu -s 'Important information' -f sample_file

or

    ./smtp -m tservo@gizmonic.cs.umd.edu -t ctrobot@gizmonic.cs.umd.edu -s 'This is funny' -f sample_fileB far_side.jpg

